Govt to release Rythu Bandhu funds from Dec 28,"The Telangana government has decided to commence distribution of farm investment support of Rs 5,000 per acre to the eligible farmers in the ensuing Rabi (Yasangi) season under the Rythu Bandhu scheme from December 28. It required Rs 7,500 crore to disburse the benefit to more than 55 lakh farmers in the current season. In view of financial constraints, the farm input incentive will be deposited first in the bank accounts of the farmers with one acre or less. Later, the amount will be given to the peasants who own land up to 10 acres. The process of depositing the money in the bank accounts of farmers will be completed by the end of Sankranti festival. Chief Minister K Chandrashekhar Rao on Sunday directed Finance Minister T Harish Rao to start releasing the crop investment - Rythu Bandhu -- funds for the Yasangi harvest season and ensure the availability of adequate funds for the scheme. Sources said the Union government has stopped the release of nearly Rs 40,000 crore funds to Telangana under various schemes and programmes. As a result, the state government has been struggling hard to meet the financial requirements in the current financial year. Officials of the State Finance department said the government will mobilize funds through institutional borrowings within the FRMB limit and transfer the money to the scheme. State Finance Secretary Ramakrishna Rao has been asked to accord priority to the scheme and release the funds by January end.","The Telangana government will begin distributing Rs 5,000 per acre to eligible farmers under the Rythu Bandhu scheme for the upcoming Rabi (Yasangi) season starting December 28. Over 55 lakh farmers will benefit, with the total requirement estimated at Rs 7,500 crore. Due to financial constraints, payments will first be made to farmers owning one acre or less, followed by those with up to 10 acres, with all disbursements expected by the Sankranti festival. Chief Minister K Chandrashekhar Rao directed Finance Minister T Harish Rao to ensure adequate funds for the scheme despite a delay in nearly Rs 40,000 crore in central government releases to Telangana. The state plans to mobilize funds through institutional borrowings within financial limits to meet the scheme's requirements by the end of January.",National News,2022-12-19 00:00:00
"Transparency, Trust, and Security Needs for the Design of Digital News Authentication Tools","Americans' trust in news is declining, and authenticity and transparency challenges in digital publishing contexts pose unique challenges to the ability to effectively gratify their information-seeking needs via online media. Cryptographic technologies and web-based provenance indicators have the potential to enhance the trustworthiness and transparency of digital communication, but better understandings of news consumers practices and needs are required to develop practical tools. Through a representative online survey of 400 digital news consumers and 19 follow-up interviews, we investigate how users authenticate and assign trust to news content, and identify specific needs pertaining to news transparency and authentication that could be met by digital news authentication tools. While many users currently rely on political ideology to assess news trustworthiness, we find that users of all political orientations see value in independent provenance and authentication tools for digital news.","This study likely delves into the essential aspects of designing digital tools for authenticating news sources, with a focus on transparency, trustworthiness, and security. The research probably explores the key requirements and considerations needed to develop effective mechanisms for verifying the authenticity of digital news content. These considerations likely involve transparency in the authentication process, building trust among users, and ensuring robust security measures to prevent misinformation and disinformation. By addressing these needs, the research aims to contribute to the development of tools that can help users distinguish between reliable and unreliable news sources in the digital landscape. Specific findings and details would require access to the full study.",Miscellaneous,2023-04-07 00:00:00
A mistake': Donald Trump says Secret Service did not warn him about...,"Days after surviving an assassination attempt, former US President Donald Trump has claimed that the Secret Service did not warn him about gunman Thomas Matthew Crooks before the assassination attempt. He claimed agents had eyed the attacker hours before the attack but they did not mention it. “Nobody mentioned it,” Trump told Jesse Watters in an upcoming episode of the Fox News anchor’s primetime show. Trump was shot in the ear less than 10 minutes into his speech, prompting him to be escorted off stage. One attendee and the shooter died during the attack while two others were injured. “[They] could’ve said, ‘Let’s wait for 15, 20 minutes, 5 minutes.’ Nobody said…I think that was a mistake,” he added. Trump has also dismissed concerns raised by critics that he is a threat to democracy, telling a large crowd in Michigan that he “took a bullet for democracy.” In the rally in Michigan on Saturday, Trump, who is the Republican presidential nominee for the November 5 elections, was joined by his running mate J D Vance. Trump also alleged that the rival Democratic Party is trying to overthrow the results of their primaries to dump incumbent President Joe Biden from the ballot. “Couldn't happen to a nicer guy. As you're seeing, the Democrat Party is not the party of democracy. They're really the enemies of democracy,” he said.","Former US President Donald Trump has claimed that the Secret Service failed to warn him about the gunman who attempted to assassinate him, despite allegedly eyeing the attacker hours before the incident. Trump stated that no one mentioned the potential threat, and that the agents could have delayed his speech to prevent the attack. Trump was shot in the ear during the incident, which resulted in the death of one attendee and the shooter, as well as injuries to two others. Trump has also dismissed concerns that he poses a threat to democracy, instead claiming that he ""took a b