 believe this accumulation will maintain positive momentum in the stock above said levels. The delivery Z-Score has again started to move into the positive territory since last month as the stock is witnessing fresh accumulation in the delivery segment,” analysts added. ICICI Direct sees a three-month time frame for this stock with a stop loss at Rs 97.8 per share. Rakesh Jhunjhunwala and Rekha Jhunjhunwala own 7,57,21,060 equity shares of Federal Bank or a 3.64% stake in the lender. The value of the big bull’s stake in the company stands at Rs 832.9 crore on Wednesday morning.","ICICI Direct analysts believe that Federal Bank, owned by Rakesh Jhunjhunwala, could see a 13% rally in the next three months, targeting Rs 124 per share. The stock has performed well, rising 26% this year to trade at Rs 110 per share. The analysts expect the banking sector, especially Federal Bank, to continue performing well despite potential consolidation in the Nifty. The stock has shown resilience, rising 18% in July alone, and positive indicators on the options and delivery fronts support the outlook for further gains.",Business and Finance,2022-08-03 00:00:00
