nded over to district administration for relief, while the remaining amount will be given to the Orissa State Disaster Mitigation Authority (OSDMA), sources said. The administration was directed to submit a report of damages, in violence following the August 23 killing of VHP leader swami Laxmananda Saraswati, at the earliest as a high-level team of officials visited the district today to assess and inspect relief work, they said. — PTI","Fresh violence erupted in Orissa's riot-hit Kandhamal district, with 80 houses torched despite efforts to contain the situation. Government officials, including the home secretary and DGP, visited the area to assess damage and accelerate relief efforts. Over 19,000 people sought refuge in relief camps. The state government sanctioned Rs 2 crore for relief operations.",Crime and Justice,2008-09-02 00:00:00
