eged misbehaviour of officers. They have written to the Director General of Police, stating that the behaviour and language used by the police during the raids is unfortunate and inexcusable, and that such actions are a wider problem affecting ordinary citizens. The activists have called for strong action against the personnel involved and a review of the police training system to ensure that officers develop a habit of using decent language and behaviour with the public.",Crime and Justice,2004-12-27 00:00:00
