Activists hanker after more,"NEW DELHI: The cabinet decision may have attempted to disable the Right to Information Act but that has not stopped activist Aruna Roy from using the same legislation to pack in a punch. She has requested the cabinet secretariat for details based on which the cabinet decided- to omit file notings except those related to social and developmental projects- from the purview of the RTI act. In an application filed with the cabinet secretariat on Monday, Roy has asked for ""the decisions of the council of ministers, the reasons thereof, and the material on the basis of which the decisions were taken, relating to amendments to be made in the Right to Information Act of 2005."" The controversial decision- to allow file notings related only to social and developmental work to be made public-has stirred a hornet's nest. While social activists have described the move to tinker with a legislation that has been enforced for less than a year, the government has tried to paint the move as a progressive one. File notings have become such a point of debate because of their importance. It is these notes that hold the rationale for government actions, or the lack of it, change in certain policy, why a certain contract is given or why a sanction was withheld to prosecute a particular corrupt official. Mazdoor Kisan Shakti Sangathan's Nikhil Dey said that the bureaucrats were ke-en on removing file notings, especially those relating to personnel related matters, from the view of the public. ""It is a well-known fact that postings and appointments in the government are done mainly on the basis of patronage and influence. Those who preside over the RTI act do not want to lose this power of patronage and start becoming answerable for their actions,"" Dey said. He added that despite public statements to the contrary, government did not want to give up its privilege to continue functioning ""arbitrarily and secretively."" The government on the other hand has been caught on the backfoot.At pains to prove that the amendment was not a case of regression the PMO insisted that ""only a small portion of file notings will now remain exempted from disclosure. This is related to subjects that are already exempted under sub-Section (1) of Section 8 of the Act and to personnel-related matters like examination, assessment and evaluation for recruitment, disciplinary proceedings.","Activist Aruna Roy utilizes the Right to Information Act to challenge the cabinet's decision to exclude certain file notings from RTI purview. The move sparks controversy, with activists criticizing it as regressive and the government defending it as progressive, citing exemptions related to personnel matters and specific subjects.",GOVT POLICIES,2006-08-01 00:00:00
The Best Photographers of Day,"The image captures participants running on the iconic Bandra-Worli Sea Link during the 2017 Mumbai Marathon. The Bandra-Worli Sea Link is a prominent landmark in Mumbai, connecting the western suburbs of Bandra and the Worli area in South Mumbai. It is a cable-stayed bridge that spans across the Arabian Sea, offering breathtaking views of the Mumbai skyline. In January, during the Mumbai Marathon, the Bandra-Worli Sea Link serves as one of the key routes for the marathon course. Runners from various parts of the world participate in the marathon, making it one of the largest and most prestigious running events in Asia. The participants in the image are seen running along the bridge, with the majestic sea and cityscape in the background. The atmosphere during the marathon is one of energy, determination, and camaraderie as participants push themselves to complete the race. The Mumbai Marathon is not only a platform for showcasing athletic prowess but also serves as a symbol of unity and community spirit. It brings together people from diverse backgrounds, all striving towards a common goal of fitness and achievement. Overall, the image captures a moment of athleticism and urban beauty against the backdrop of the Bandra-Worli Sea Link, highlighting the vibrancy of Mumbai's culture and the spirit of the city's marathon.","The image depicts participants running on the Bandra-Worli Sea Link during the 2017 Mumbai Marathon, a prestigious event attracting runners globally. The bridge, a notable Mumbai landmark, connects Bandra and Worli, offering panoramic views of the city skyline and Arabian Sea. Amidst the January marathon, the sea link serves as a key route, embodying energy, determination, and camaraderie among runners. The event symbolizes unity and community spirit, uniting diverse individuals in pursuit of fitness and achievement. The marathon showcases athletic prowess while celebrating Mumbai's vibrant culture. Against the backdrop 