10 Android apps ‘popular’ among smartphone users across the world for meditation,"Mindfulness and meditation have become essential tools for maintaining mental health and well-being in today's fast-paced world. As more people seek ways to reduce stress and enhance their quality of life, meditation apps have surged in popularity, becoming a staple on many smartphones globally. These apps offer a convenient and accessible way to practice meditation, featuring guided sessions, calming soundscapes, and personalised programs to suit various needs and preferences. Here, we have explored 10 free Android apps that have captured the attention of users around the world, making them popular choices (with more than a million downloads) for those looking to incorporate meditation into their daily routines. Calm (Calm.com, Inc. -- 50 million+ downloads) Calm offers an extensive library of guided meditations, Sleep Stories, and soundscapes designed to help manage stress, improve sleep, and enhance overall mental health. With features catering to both beginners and seasoned meditators, Calm supports users in incorporating mindfulness into their daily lives, providing tools for anxiety relief, mood balancing, and self-care through a variety of accessible programs and activities. Headspace: Mindful Meditation (Headspace for Meditation, Mindfulness and Sleep -- 10 million+ downloads) Headspace is a mindfulness and meditation app designed to help users manage stress, anxiety, and sleep issues. It offers guided meditations, sleep stories and breathwork exercises aimed at improving mental and physical well-being. The app includes daily meditation routines, sleep aids, and mindfulness exercises suitable for all experience levels, providing a personal meditation studio to support users anytime, anywhere. Meditopia: Sleep & Meditation (Meditopia -- 10 million+ downloads) Meditopia sets itself apart as a mental health app by offering more than quick fixes for sleep or stress. It provides over 1000 in-depth meditations and breathing exercises in 12 languages, covering a broad range of human experiences such as relationships, self-acceptance, and personal growth. Meditopia aims to be a sanctuary for mental resilience and peace, offering tools for long-term healing and happiness. Insight Timer - Meditation App (Insight Network Inc -- 5 million+ downloads) Insight Timer is one of the top free meditation apps that features guided meditations, sleep music, and talks from experts across prestigious institutions. With over 100,000 free resources, and new additions daily, it supports millions globally in achieving deeper sleep, stress management, and mindfulness, appealing to both beginners and seasoned meditators. Let's Meditate: Relax & Sleep (Let's Meditate Team -- 1 million+ downloads) This meditation app features a simple, easy-to-use design with a clutter-free interface, allowing users to just select a track and play. It offers a wide variety of guided meditations on topics like anxiety, sleep, and healing, available in both short and long durations. Users can download tracks for offline listening without worrying about ads or sign-ups, preserving a soothing user experience. Serenity: Guided Meditation (Olson Meditation and Mindfulness Apps -- 1 million+ downloads) Serenity: Guided Meditation offers a variety of meditation and mindfulness techniques to bring peace and happiness. Learn with a free 7-day audio course, then expand your skills with Foundations. Sleep guides and stress relief meditations help calm the mind, while quick sessions offer serenity. No sign-up is needed, ideal for beginners, with additional content available through one-time purchases or a subscription. Features include daily reminders, challenges, progress tracking, and more. Smiling Mind: Meditation App (Smiling Mind -- 1 million+ downloads) Smiling Mind is a free app developed by psychologists and educators. The app features meditation and mindfulness programs for all ages, aiming to build mental fitness, improve relationships, reduce stress, and enhance emotional skills. Offline access, mood tracking, and dark mode are included. Balance: Meditation & Sleep (Elevate Labs -- 1 million+ downloads) Balance Meditation and Sleep app offers personalised meditation programs to improve mental health, reduce anxiety, and enhance focus. With a free year of access, users can access guided meditations, sleep aids, and relaxation exercises. The app's features include 10-day plans, single meditations, and sleep relaxation exercises. Subscription options are available after the free trial. Medito: Meditation & Sleep (Medito for Mindfulness, Meditation and Sleep -- 1 million+ downloads) Medito is a free meditation app offering guided meditations, breathing exercises, and mindfulness practices for improved mental well-being. With courses designed for both beginners and advanced users, Medito helps create a calm headspace. It features sleep meditations, learning courses, and content from organisations like UCLA. The app is a non-profit initiative, aiming to improve access to mental health tools. Medito offers comprehensive courses, daily meditations, sleep support, and learning packs, with content on various themes like stress management and mindfulness. Aura: Meditation & Sleep, CBT (Aura Health - Mindfulness, Sleep, Meditations -- 1 million+ downloads) Aura: Meditation & Sleep, CBT is a top-rated app offering personalised guided meditations, mindfulness coaching, CBT, and sleep aids. With a vast library of content, including sleep sounds and stories, Aura helps with stress, anxiety, sleep, and self-improvement.","The article discusses the rising popularity of mindfulness and meditation apps in today's hectic world, focusing on 10 free Android apps with over a million downloads each. These apps offer a range of features like guided meditations, sleep aids, stress relief techniques, and personalized programs for mental well-being. Calm and Headspace are highlighted for their comprehensive libraries and user-friendly interfaces, while Meditopia stands out for its in-depth content on various life aspects. Insight Timer offers a vast resource of free meditations and talks from experts. Let's Meditate provides a simple interface with offline listening options. Serenity offers a structured learning approach, while Smiling Mind caters to all ages with programs designed by psychologists. Balance and Medito focus on personalized meditation plans, and Aura provides a holistic approach with CBT, sleep aids, and mindfulness coaching. These apps collectively aim to make meditation and mindfulness accessible and beneficial for users seeking to manage stress, improve sleep, and enhance their overall mental health.",Science and Technology,2024-04-28 00:00:00
John Abraham's next with Rohit Shetty based on former Mumbai Police Commissioner? - Details Inside,"John Abraham and Rohit Shetty are all set to team up for a powerful new project that blends real-life drama with the director’s signature action-packed storytelling. As per the latest reports, this untitled film is inspired by the life and career of former Mumbai Police Commissioner Rakesh Maria. Inspired by a true life story As reported by Mid-Day, the film draws its inspiration from Maria’s autobiography, ‘Let Me Say It Now’, and is set to chronicle his journey from being a young boy from Bandra to becoming one of the most respected cops in India. The script reads like a thriller, with intense moments from some of Mumbai’s darkest chapters – including the 1993 Bombay blasts and the 26/11 terror attacks. The report revealed that the film would follow his journey and focus on his deep connection with Mumbai and the vital role he played in safeguarding the city during the terror attacks. John Abraham defends 'The Diplomat' after ban in the Middle East: ‘Not an anti-Pakistan film’ A truth-driven cop Universe from Rohit ShettyKnown for his gripping and glossy cop dramas like 'Singham', 'Simmba', and 'Sooryavanshi', Rohit is now taking a different route. This time, the drama is grounded in real-life events. As an insider told the portal, “Rohit always wanted to make a cop film rooted in truth. Rakesh Maria’s life reads like a thriller. It’s intense and has many high points, from his investigation of the 1993 Bombay blasts and the 26/11 attacks to his brush with the underworld. Maria and Shetty have been in talks for a while, and it’s finally starting now.” The first leg of the shoot will focus on Maria’s early days in the police force. A dedicated team of about 150 crew members, including prosthetic specialists, research teams, and action coordinators, will be on set to ensure authenticity in storytelling and aesthetics. The team is even constructing a detailed set of the