ihar to integrate 836 Class 6–12 schools under PM‑SHRI scheme to align with NEP,"“In keeping with the mandate of the National Education Policy (NEP) 2020, Bihar has now moved ahead to integrate Class 6–12 under one academic and administrative unit, while Class 1–5 will be treated as primary school.” The PM‑SHRI scheme (Prime Minister’s Schools for Rising India), launched in 2022, will cover 836 government schools in Bihar, aligning them with NEP’s holistic, experiential, and flexible learning ethos. These schools will follow the 5+3+3+4 curricular structure, adopt activity-based and multilingual instruction, establish theme-based learning spaces, and receive infrastructure upgrades—funded jointly by the Centre and state (60:40 ratio). A state-level Quality Assessment Framework (SQAF) will monitor school performance, and district officials will ensure smooth implementation from the 2025–26 academic session onward.","On February 18, 2025, Hindustan Times reported that Bihar is integrating 836 Class 6–12 schools under the PM‑SHRI scheme to bring them in line with NEP 2020. The initiative introduces the 5+3+3+4 curriculum structure, interactive multilingual teaching, and modern, theme-based infrastructure. Schools will be evaluated under Bihar’s SQAF and funded via a 60:40 Centre–State partnership. Launching in the 2025–26 session, this effort marks a major stride in implementing NEP’s vision of holistic, experiential education at scale.",Education,2025-02-18 00:00:00
